"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9e0b7a",
"children":[
"Panic attacks are characterized by sudden onset and rapid escalation of extreme fear or anxiety along with at least four of the following:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1adce3",
"children":[
"fear of dying"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"89f9fe",
"children":[
"fear of losing control"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"2edcc5",
"children":[
"palpitations, diaphoresis, tremor, dyspnea, choking sensation"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"6e7840",
"children":[
"chest pain, nausea, dizziness, chills or heat sensations"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7d5feb",
"children":[
"paresthesia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"6a0fed",
"children":[
"derealization (perception that the world is not real)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"329915",
"children":[
"Panic disorder involves recurrent, unexpected panic attacks and persistent worry about future attacks."
]
}
]
},
